The paper discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for anomaly detection, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. Based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these are the areas where GANs are commonly used. The paper also mentions the challenge of correctly classifying anomalies, which suggests that it may be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deal with issues related to classification and detection.
